                    <span class="eyebrow">07 — STILL WONDERING</span>
                    <h2>Questions, answered</h2>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-list">
                <div class="faq-item open">
                    <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="true"
                        ><span class="q-mark"></span>Do I need to know how to solder?<span
                            class="q-num">01</span
                        ></button
                    >
                    <div class="faq-a">
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                No. Every connection on the Buddy System is solderless — cards slot
                                into keyed bays and signals route through jumper wires on the
                                breadboard. If you can plug in a USB cable, you can build your first
                                patch.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"
                        ><span class="q-mark"></span>Is it really Eurorack-compatible?<span
                            class="q-num">02</span
                        ></button
                    >
                    <div class="faq-a">
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                The base unit fits standard Eurorack dimensions and power, so you
                                can drop it into a rack you already own. The Buddy Cards themselves
                                use our own 6-pin bay, but level-shifted and CV-friendly cards
                                bridge to the rest of your system.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"
                        ><span class="q-mark"></span>Which microcontroller does it use?<span
                            class="q-num">03</span
                        ></button
                    >
                    <div class="faq-a">
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                You choose. The host MCU mounts to the Buddy Base — Daisy Seed,
                                Teensy, RP2040, STM32, or any Arduino-compatible board. The Buddy
                                Bus Protocol is deliberately platform-independent, so your firmware
                                stays yours.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"
                        ><span class="q-mark"></span>Can I design my own card?<span class="q-num"
                            >04</span
                        ></button
                    >
                    <div class="faq-a">
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                Absolutely — that's the point. The bus, pinout, and protocol are
                                public. Community cards carry a copper keybar and a BD-X designator.
                                Start from the open design language and your card will look like it
                                belongs from day one.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"
                        ><span class="q-mark"></span>When can I actually buy one?<span class="q-num"
                            >05</span
                        ></button
                    >
                    <div class="faq-a">
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                We're finalizing the first production run now. Join the waitlist and
                                you'll be first to hear when base units and the launch card families
                                are available — no spam, just one note when it's real.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

